Based on mxcl's work here: https://gist.github.com/149491/

SYNC2 is a based on a ruby script that uses FSevents API and rsync to sync 
changes from the local file system to a remote location. This linux version 
allow you to run SYNC2 as a daemon service.

* ruby gems must be installed on your system.

To install ruby gems:
$ curl -O http://files.rubyforge.vm.bytemark.co.uk/rubygems/rubygems-1.3.5.tgz
$ tar xzvf rubygems-1.3.5.tgz
$ cd rubygems-1.3.5
$ sudo /usr/bin/ruby setup.rb
$ sudo gem install rb-fsevent



